&lt;p&gt;Odeko is on a mission to continuously develop technology to champion your neighborhood cafes, coffee shops, and other independent F&amp;amp;B establishments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Local coffee shops and cafes are the backbone of any given community, and we’re here to help manage the day-to-day tasks with a platform so intuitive, it’s kinda like magic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Odeko team is diverse, passionate, and innovative. Our 400+ employees are spread across numerous departments and business lines, but are single-minded in our mission to develop technology to support the many needs of our customers. We believe that small businesses need support now more than ever, and that Odeko is uniquely positioned to provide that support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;css-u74ql7 eu4oa1w0&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;jd-appended-job-description&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;jd-section-employer&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;jd-description-text&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;ICQA&lt;/strong&gt;, you will ensure the accuracy, efficiency, and optimization of inventory management and warehouse operations within our EWR1 facility. You will oversee inventory control processes, lead replenishment activities, manage bin zones, and ensure compliance with quality standards. This role requires a detail-oriented individual with strong analytical skills, a passion for process improvement, and the ability to lead a team toward operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;What You&#39;ll Own&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory Replenishment &amp;amp; Zone Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;You&#39;ll keep our pick zones stocked and optimized — fast-movers in PICK-A, slower items in PICK-B, and every bin zone (REPLENS, NON-PK, CHILLED, BULK) configured and current. When the floor needs inventory, it&#39;s there.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Replenishment Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;Using the Replenishment Dashboard, you&#39;ll direct daily stock moves based on demand forecasts, coordinate replenishment windows around picking hours, and escalate discrepancies before they become problems.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Replenishment Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;You&#39;ll keep NetSuite bin records accurate, run mass configuration updates via CSV with the OE team, and resolve inventory discrepancies through proper adjustment workflows.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stock Counts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;You&#39;ll lead daily cycle counts — setting windows, approving results promptly, and investigating any variance over 5 units with a recount and root cause analysis. You&#39;ll also train and certify your counters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;You&#39;ll continuously refine replenishment and counting processes, build SOPs, mentor your team, and deliver clear reports and leadership updates on inventory health and operational performance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You Bring&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years in a warehouse, distribution, or inventory environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel skills — pivot tables, VLOOKUPs, data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with inventory management system

